John T. Gast

              —
              SINEAD MEMORY TAPE (2015)
            
              (5 Gate Temple)
description:
From one reggae lover to another; John T. Gast pays heartfelt homage to departed angel Sinead O’Connor with a gorgeous hour of screwed ambient dub meditation. RIYL DJ Screw, Romance, 0PN’s Eccojams, Florian TM Zeisig, Malibu

Sinead O’Connor (b. 1966, ✝ 2023) was a ubiquitous influence and hero to many who grew up in the ’80s, ‘90s and beyond. O’Connor was also a noted fan of reggae and dub, and her 1992 SNL rendition of Bob Marley’s ‘War’, with lyrics altered to reflect child abuse in... more

label: Millions Of Brilliant Idiots
description:
Killer twelve from German producer Joyride, making his debut with eight tracks of crooked beat fusions for the newly minted Millions Of Brilliant Idiots label. Falling just short of glitch music, yet full of hyperactive, angular edits, 'Joyride' shreds 8-bit melodies with crunchy, squashed beats and a bank of unpredictable samples to sound something like Mouse On Mars meets Team Doyobi round at Black To Comm's place. Ace - make sure to check.

Rainy Miller & Space Afrika

              A Grisaille Wedding

label: Fixed Abode
description:
Space Afrika and Rainy Miller mesh traces of burnt trip-hop, concrète ambience and industrialised drill on their debut collaborative full-length, offering an idiosyncratic, historically seasoned silhouette of the urban sprawl. Featuring Voice Actor, Mica Levi, Iceboy Violet, Coby Sey, Richie Culver, RenzNiro and bobbieorkid.

label: AN1MA
description:
Very, very good set of the stealthiest dark ambient-pop and trip hop creep by London’s Rest Symbol, one of a striking new clutch on the AN1MA label which has quietly emerged and held attentions since 2021 - RIYL Leslie Winer, bassæ, Tricky, John T. Gast

title_full:
Static Cleaner Lost Reward

              —
              Breathing Under Honey
            
              (Low Company)
label: Low Company
description:
The end is finally here for Low Company the label, clocking off with a full album from Tarquin Manek, one of the most prolific, distinct and perhaps under-recognised producers in our orbit. If bezonked, subaquatic dub-pop zoners are your thing, anything from The Skaters to Swell Maps, YL Hooi to Carla dal Forno, CS + Kreme to Jac Berrocal, this one’s for you.
